DISCUSSION (not code) — data retention & storage: Neon does NOT auto-delete data; a free project persists until you delete it. Caveats: (1) a fully-idle free project can be *suspended* (auto-resumes on next connect); (2) the free tier caps at 0.5 GB. Text data (hours, notes, grades) is tiny — many years for a couple students. Photos were the risk; now fixed (see below).
DISCUSSION (not code) — storage worry for two people a year: TEXT records are tiny — you will not hit 0.5 GB in a year, even for several families. PHOTOS: NOW FIXED — proof-of-work photos are stored (base64, compressed) in Postgres so they survive redeploys. (Used to go to the container's ephemeral disk.) If photo volume ever grows, move them to free object storage (Cloudflare R2 / Backblaze B2) and keep only the URL in Neon.
